 The passenger side floor section took me between 2 and 2.5 hours to replace
 on the '60.
 
 Also - do you have the pedal pan on your bus?  It makes a *huge* difference
 in draft reduction!
 
 Although I haven't done it on this bus yet, I found that replacing the
 factory heater tube wrap with foam pipe insulation, as well as insulating
 the curved sections fore and aft that are not normally insulated, helped
 considerably with heat.
 
